This exercise is to show branch efficiency because of the divergent code.
because of the divergent code the path of the execution changes and few threads executes different instructions then regular flow.
That causes some inefficiency in the execution path.
3 types of warp
1) Active:- Currently running on GPU
2) stalled Wrap:- Not read for execution
3) Eligible Wrap:- Not executing but ready for execution.  

Commands to show inefficiency:
nvcc -G -o divergence branch.cu
nvprof --metrics divergence
